Warcraft III PvPGN Launcher
Third-party components

This launcher is MIT-licensed (see LICENSE). It does not contain any Warcraft
III game data: the game is downloaded at runtime from Blizzard Entertainment's
own official free "legacy" installer (us.battle.net/download/getLegacy) and is
never redistributed by this project.

The launcher bundles the following third-party binaries, which it unpacks next
to the game so Warcraft III can connect to a PvPGN server and render under Wine.
Each remains under its own license, reproduced or pointed to below.

================================================================================
1. W3L loader: w3l.exe, w3lh.dll, wl27.dll
   Purpose: patches Warcraft III's logon so it can connect to a PvPGN server
            instead of Blizzard's Battle.net.
   License: GNU General Public License (GPL).
   Source:  The W3L loader is a PvPGN-community project. Corresponding source is
            available from the PvPGN community distribution (cdn.pvpgn.pro / the
            pvpgn project). For a copy of the corresponding source for the exact
            build bundled here, open an issue on this repository and it will be
            provided.

            (The GPL requires a source offer that anyone receiving the binary
            can actually act on, so this names a route that works for whoever
            has the binary, not just people who know the author.)

2. DXVK: d3d9.dll
   Purpose: translates Direct3D 9 to Vulkan so the game renders reliably on
            Linux/Wine (NVIDIA/Wayland).
   License: zlib/libpng license.
   Source:  https://github.com/doitsujin/dxvk
   Copyright (c) 2017 Philip Rebohle and DXVK contributors.

3. d3d8to9: d3d8.dll
   Purpose: translates Warcraft III's Direct3D 8 calls to Direct3D 9 (fed into
            DXVK above).
   License: MIT License.
   Source:  https://github.com/crosire/d3d8to9
   Copyright (c) 2015 Patrick Mours.

